{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_2788be2d5ffe53nFnIn5eNbziE","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d877431e9001d9Kvr6PUMGHCaz","parts":[{"id":"prt_d87743a02001ZM6gehJ23rhyd9","messageID":"msg_d877431e9001d9Kvr6PUMGHCaz","sessionID":"ses_2788be2d5ffe53nFnIn5eNbziE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_296702d53b83426cb8c80df7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.rst</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: ******\n2: Mopidy\n3: ******\n4: \n5: `Mopidy`_ is an extensible music server written in Python.\n6: \n7: Mopidy plays music from local disk, Spotify, SoundCloud, Google Play Music, and\n8: more. You edit the playlist from any phone, tablet, or computer using a variety\n9: of MPD and web clients.\n10: \n11: **Stream music from the cloud**\n12: \n13: Vanilla Mopidy only plays music from files and radio streams.  Through\n14: `extensions`_, Mopidy can play music from cloud services like Spotify,\n15: SoundCloud, and Google Play Music.\n16: With Mopidy's extension support, backends for new music sources can be easily\n17: added.\n18: \n19: **Mopidy is just a server**\n20: \n21: Mopidy is a Python application that runs in a terminal or in the background on\n22: Linux computers or Macs that have network connectivity and audio output.\n23: Out of the box, Mopidy is an HTTP server. If you install the `Mopidy-MPD`_\n24: extension, it becomes an MPD server too. Many additional frontends for\n25: controlling Mopidy are available as extensions.\n26: \n27: **Pick your favorite client**\n28: \n29: You and the people around you can all connect their favorite MPD or web client\n30: to the Mopidy server to search for music and manage the playlist together.\n31: With a browser or MPD client, which is available for all popular operating\n32: systems, you can control the music from any phone, tablet, or computer.\n33: \n34: **Mopidy on Raspberry Pi**\n35: \n36: The `Raspberry Pi`_ is a popular device to run Mopidy on, either using\n37: Raspberry Pi OS, Ubuntu, or Arch Linux.\n38: Pimoroni recommends Mopidy for use with their `Pirate Audio`_ audio gear for\n39: Raspberry Pi.\n40: Mopidy is also a significant building block in the `Pi Musicbox`_ integrated\n41: audio jukebox system for Raspberry Pi.\n42: \n43: **Mopidy is hackable**\n44: \n45: Mopidy's extension support and Python, JSON-RPC, and JavaScript APIs make\n46: Mopidy a perfect base for your projects.\n47: In one hack, a Raspberry Pi was embedded in an old cassette player. The buttons\n48: and volume control are wired up with GPIO on the Raspberry Pi, and are used to\n49: control playback through a custom Mopidy extension. The cassettes have NFC tags\n50: used to select playlists from Spotify.\n51: \n52: .. _Mopidy: https://mopidy.com/\n53: .. _extensions: https://mopidy.com/ext/\n54: .. _Mopidy-MPD: https://mopidy.com/ext/mpd/\n55: .. _Raspberry Pi: https://www.raspberrypi.org/\n56: .. _Pirate Audio: https://shop.pimoroni.com/collections/pirate-audio\n57: .. _Pi Musicbox: https://pimusicbox.github.io/\n58: \n59: \n60: **Getting started**\n61: \n62: To get started with Mopidy, begin by reading the\n63: `installation docs <https://docs.mopidy.com/en/latest/installation/>`_.\n64: \n65: \n66: **Contributing**\n67: \n68: Begin by reading the\n69: `contributing <https://docs.mopidy.com/en/latest/contributing/>`_\n70: section of our documentation.\n71: If you are a developer, please also read\n72: `Development environment <https://docs.mopidy.com/en/latest/devenv/>`_\n73: and/or\n74: `Extension development <https://docs.mopidy.com/en/latest/extensiondev/>`_.\n75: We welcome all kinds of help with bug fixing, testing, documentation, and supporting other users.\n76: \n77: \n78: **Project resources**\n79: \n80: - `Documentation <https://docs.mopidy.com/>`_\n81: - `Discourse forum <https://discourse.mopidy.com/>`_\n82: - `Zulip chat <https://mopidy.zulipchat.com/>`_\n83: - `Source code <https://github.com/mopidy/mopidy>`_\n84: - `Issue tracker <https://github.com/mopidy/mopidy/issues>`_\n85: \n86: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/mopidy\n87:     :target: https://pypi.org/project/mopidy/\n88:     :alt: Latest PyPI version\n89: \n90: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/mopidy/mopidy/ci.yml\n91:     :target: https://github.com/mopidy/mopidy/actions/workflows/ci.yml\n92:     :alt: CI build status\n93: \n94: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/readthedocs/mopidy\n95:     :target: https://docs.mopidy.com/\n96:     :alt: Read the Docs build status\n97: \n98: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/github/mopidy/mopidy\n99:     :target: https://codecov.io/gh/mopidy/mopidy\n100:     :alt: Test coverage\n101: \n102: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/badge/chat-on%20zulip-brightgreen\n103:     :target: https://mopidy.zulipchat.com/\n104:     :alt: Chat on Zulip\n\n(End of file - total 104 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"******\nMopidy\n******\n\n`Mopidy`_ is an extensible music server written in Python.\n\nMopidy plays music from local disk, Spotify, SoundCloud, Google Play Music, and\nmore. You edit the playlist from any phone, tablet, or computer using a variety\nof MPD and web clients.\n\n**Stream music from the cloud**\n\nVanilla Mopidy only plays music from files and radio streams.  Through\n`extensions`_, Mopidy can play music from cloud services like Spotify,\nSoundCloud, and Google Play Music.\nWith Mopidy's extension support, backends for new music sources can be easily\nadded.\n\n**Mopidy is just a server**\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.rst","time":{"start":1776094034709,"end":1776094034722}}}]}
